node.text:
The #Philippines government has laws in place which are meant to protect the environment, pollution is still a major problem. 

Love, one of our participants from the #YOUTHPOWERHACKS, is on a mission to change the way her country deals with this issue. There are several factors which must be addressed to combat pollution – listen to Love’s voice note to find out what they are. 

#Goal13 @restlessdevelopment @theglobalgoals
Les deje un mensajito por interno @unilever

@unilever your products have polluted the planet for decades, our natural environments have been devastated by your plastic. All to make profit for your share holders and now you demand that governments and tax payers money is used to fix your problem. And you use the voice of a citizen to highlight the plight. Your company could help that citizen more than most. How about you use that 9billion profit to tidy up your mess? How much money are you using to clean up the plastic in our oceans? Can you please tell us us the exact figures. @oneglobalocean
@unilever you guys need to do 1000x more to address the plastic pollution problem that YOU among several other companies have caused !!!!!! DO WAY MORE.
@hotties4change @1000 x would just be the beginning.
